cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel localized multi-view subspace clustering model that considers the confidence levels of both views and samples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Among these, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category as the paper proposes a new clustering model that involves assigning weights to samples and views, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper also mentions experimental results, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to the machine learning sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible as they involve similar techniques and applications.
